Hippos! Hippos! Hippos! 
.
The hippo is the third largest land animal and on average an adult male weighs in at nearly 1500 kilograms on average.
There are large numbers of hippo in the Masai Mara National Reserve. Male hippos (bulls) rule over a particular stretch of river and generally have five to 30 female hippos and their young to watch over.

Just visited this small village Konerirajapuram (original name is ThiruNallam), the temple of Umamaheswarar-Mangalanayaki, and I'm in awe! The spiritual ambiance left me feeling truly blessed. And the cherry on top was the world's largest 'swayambu' bronze Natarajar - simply magnificent! 

This temple is also considered as the 6th Sabai - the Rudraksha Sabai. Decorated with a huge mandapam using rudhrakshams.

The present temple was constructed in the 10th century AD by Sembian Mahadevi, grandmother of Raja Raja Chola I. The history of this temple is also a very goosebumpy story.

The frescos in the temple hall from the 8th century Chozha period are truly a priceless treasure, depicting stories of gods, goddesses, and the common man. However, it breaks my heart to see the damage caused to these masterpieces over the years due to neglect and lack of proper maintenance, and some portions have been completely destroyed.
It's a stark reminder of the importance of preserving our heritage for future generations.

Can't wait to revisit and soak in more of the divine energy.

The moment I walked into the mutt, the divinity and the sanctity of this place can be easily felt. 
The Jeeva Samadhi of Sri Bodendra Saraswathi Swamigal, the 59th Peedathipathy of Kanchi mutt. One can feel the spiritual Presence of Sri Bodendral in his Adhistanam at Govindapuram.

Annadhanam is a daily ritual in this mutt. And the public and pay a reasonable amount of money for the food preparation.

Govindapuram is a beautiful, calm and serene village situated on the river bank of Veeracholan (A branch of River Cauvery) and located in between the cities of Kumbakonam And Mayiladuthurai in the Tanjore Cauvery belt of Tamilnadu.

It's been years since we have been planning to visit this temple and I guess Krishna wanted to go only now. 
OMG the beauty of the temple and the gorgeous Narthana Krishna, the sanctity of the place are all beyond words. 
I'm sure most of us who know classical Carnatic music will know this place, because of the great composer Venkata Kavi - and all his songs about this Krishna. The temple is almost 2000 years old and has such an awesome history. 
God Krishna enacted the Kalinga Narthana episode to two devine cows (Nandini and Patti), daughters of the celestial wish-yeilding cow Kamadhenu. 
Most rarest of rare temples to be visited in a lifetime. 
.
.
.

Not far from the imposing southern gopuram of Srirangam Ranganathaswamy temple, is a family-run orchard, Thathachariar Gardens, which has, since the 1940s, been synonymous with the Imam Pasand mango.

Peacocks call out in the distance as visitors squelch  at the Thathachariar Gardens in what is to me and any mother, an annual pilgrimage to seek out the sweet and soft-as-butter Imam Pasand mango that is the signature produce of this family-owned farm.

In the 70-acre farm that we visited, Thathachariar Gardens has 700 mango trees, of which around 300 are the Imam Pasand, followed by other varieties such as Banganapalli, Roumani, and Kallamani (Bangloura).

Black Orchid restobar. Let me start by raving about their Pesto Fried Mozzarella with Garlic Sauce. Oh. My. Goodness. It was an absolute flavor bomb! The mozzarella was perfectly crispy on the outside, and the pesto added a fresh and herby twist. And let's not forget the garlic sauce—it was pure magic. Creamy, garlicky, and oh-so-dreamy.

Now, let's talk about the drink of the night—the Peppertini. Talk about a unique and trendy concoction! This little number had a kick that left my taste buds tingling with delight. The combination of peppery notes and a hint of sweetness was like a party in my mouth. It was a refreshing and unexpected twist on a classic martini. Sip by sip, I found myself falling in love with this bold and daring creation.

Black Orchid restobar itself is a hip and happening spot that oozes style. The ambience is just perfect for a fun night out with friends or a romantic evening with your special someone.

Picture this: stepping into a neon wonderland that’s straight out of a retro movie.

The Neon Museum is the epitome of Vegas cool. It’s like walking through a time machine filled with neon signs that are dripping with history and style. Each sign had its own story to tell, representing the glitz and glamour of old-school Vegas. Talk about a blast from the past!

The collection was seriously mind-blowing. Neon lights flashing and buzzing, colors popping like fireworks—it was like being in a trippy art gallery.

If you’re ever in Sin City, don’t miss out on the Neon Museum. It’s a one-of-a-kind journey into the neon-lit history of Vegas.

Travel has been my teacher, showing me the beauty of diversity and the magic of new horizons. Feeling truly blessed for these experiences that have enriched my life. 🌍✈️
